methods.createRegionedColumnSource:
Create a new RegionedColumnSource appropriate to implement the supplied ColumnDefinition.
 Note: This implementation currently lets arrays fall into the catch-all (Serializable) case.
 Note: There is no handling for Enum(Set) assignables.  No existing tables should have legacy Enum(Set) columns.

Note: Java generics information - <DATA_TYPE>

:param columnDefinition: (io.deephaven.db.tables.ColumnDefinition<DATA_TYPE>) - The column definition
:param codecMappings: io.deephaven.db.v2.ColumnToCodecMappings
:return: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.regioned.RegionedColumnSource<DATA_TYPE>) A new RegionedColumnSource.
